quran[13]{c,v,t,f}:
42,32,"And of His Signs are the ships that sail in the sea like mountains."
42,33,"If He so wills, He can cause the winds to become still so that they will remain motionless on its surface. Surely there are many Signs in this for those who are wont to be steadfast and give thanks. {1}",footnotes:1:Signs for him who patiently endures
42,34,"He may, while forgiving much of the sins of those that ride these ships, drown them on account of some of their misdeeds."
42,35,"Then those who wrangle about Our Signs will come to know that there is no escape for them. {1}",footnotes:1:The Quraish
42,36,"That which has been given to you is only the wherewithal of the transient life of this world. {1} But that which is with Allah is better and more enduring {2} for those who believe and put their trust in their Lord; {3}",footnotes:1:Here
42,37,"who eschew grave sins and shameful deeds, {1} and whenever they are angry, forgive; {2}",footnotes:1:For explanation
42,38,"who obey their Lord {1} and establish Prayer; who conduct their affairs by consultation, {2} and spend out of what We have bestowed upon them; {3}",footnotes:1:Literally: “Who answer the call of their Lord”
42,39,"who, when a wrong is done to them, seek its redress. {1}",footnotes:1:This also is one of the best characteristics of the believers
42,40,"The recompense {1} of evil is evil the like of it. {2} But he who forgives and makes amends, his reward lies with Allah. {3} Surely He does not love the wrong-doers. {4}",footnotes:1:The passage from here to the end of   (verse 43) is an explanation of verse 39.|181192:This is the first fundamental principle which must be borne in mind in retaliation. The right limit of retaliation is that one should return the same sort of ill treatment that he has received; he has no right to return a greater ill treatment.|181193:This is the second principle. It means: Although it is permissible to retaliate against the one who has committed a violence
42,41,"There is no blame against him who avenges himself after he has been wronged."
42,42,"Blame attaches only to those who subject people to wrong and commit excesses on earth. A painful chastisement awaits them."
42,43,"But he who patiently endures and forgives, that is a conduct of great resolve. {1}",footnotes:1:One should note that the qualities of the believers that have been mentioned in these verses
42,44,"He whom Allah lets go astray, none after Him can be his protector. {1} You will see that when the wrong-doers observe the chastisement, they will exclaim: “Is there any way to go back?” {2}",footnotes:1:That is
